text: Arizona's 16th Legislative District is one of 30 in the state, covering portions of Maricopa and Pinal counties. As of 2018 there are 46 precincts in the district, 25 in Maricopa and 21 in Pinal, with a total registered voter population of 135,757. ==Political representation== The district is represented for the 2019-2021 Legislative Session in the State Senate by Dave Farnsworth (R) and in the House of Representatives by Kelly Townsend (R) and John Fillmore (R). ==References== Category:Maricopa County, Arizona Category:Pinal County, Arizona Category:Arizona legislative districts
title: Arizona's 16th legislative district
